Alireza Firouzja vs Magnus Carlsen
Magnus Carlsen Invitational GAME 1, 20.4.2020
Sicilian, Nimzovich-Rossolimo attack (without ...d6) (B30)

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 4. Bxc6 bxc6 5. d3 Qc7 6. Qe2 e5 7. Nbd2 Ne7 8. Nc4 Ng6 9. h4 h5 10. g3 d6 11. Bd2 f6 12. Ne3 Be7 13. Ng1 Bd8 14. Qf3 Nf8 15. Ne2 Ne6 16. Qg2 a5 17. a4 Nd4 18. f4 Be6 19. b3 Qd7 20. f5 Bf7 21. Nc1 d5 22. O-O c4 23. bxc4 dxc4 24. dxc4 Bb6 25. Rb1 Qa7 26. Kh2 Rd8 27. Rb2 O-O 28. g4 Ne2 29. Qxe2 Rxd2 30. Qxd2 Bxe3 31. Qe2 Qd4 32. Nd3 Qxe4 33. Re1 Bf4+ 34. Kh3 Qxc4 35. gxh5 Bh6 36. Rb7 Qxa4 37. Rg1 Rd8 38. Rg3 Qa1 39. Nf2 Rd2 40. Rb8+ Kh7 41. Qg4 Qf1+ 42. Rg2 Qxg2+ 43. Kxg2

World Champion Magnus Carlsen takes on world blitz no. 1 Hikaru Nakamura today in a 4-game rapid match as the $250,000 Magnus Carlsen Invitational begins. Usually that pairing would eclipse any other match, but 16-year-old Alireza Firouzja taking on world no. 3 Ding Liren is almost as mouth-watering. Can Alireza continue in the form that saw him beat Magnus in the Banter Blitz Cup final? All the games will be streamed live on chess24 with commentary in 9 languages as a new age of online chess begins.
